[medium] src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue:1003 (concurrency/races)
On first mount when dashboard-suggestions config has not been fetched yet and resolves enabled, fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig mutates dashboardSuggestionsConfigFetched/dashboardSuggestionsEnabled, which triggers the watcher above to call loadDashboardSuggestionState(). The onMounted continuation then immediately calls loadDashboardSuggestionState() again before the first in-flight call has set loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor, so both dashboard-suggestions endpoints can be requested twice for the same SSP. This violates the intended once-per-SSP fetch behavior and adds avoidable duplicate API load/state churn.
Suggested fix: Let a single path own the initial load: for example make the config/SSP watcher immediate and remove the onMounted loadDashboardSuggestionState() call, or add an in-flight request keyed by SSP so concurrent calls return the existing promise before starting another fetch.
Guidance: In src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue, fix the duplicate initial dashboard suggestion state load. The current config/SSP watcher calls loadDashboardSuggestionState() when fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig() flips dashboardSuggestionsConfigFetched/dashboardSuggestionsEnabled, and onMounted() then calls loadDashboardSuggestionState() again before loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor is set. Prefer adding an in-flight guard keyed by SSP inside loadDashboardSuggestionState(force = false): create a module-local/ref variable such as loadingDashboardSuggestionStateFor and a Promise variable such as dashboardSuggestionStateLoadPromise. After validating sspId and dashboardSuggestionsEnabled, return early when !force and loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor.value === sspId, and also return/await the existing promise when !force and loadingDashboardSuggestionStateFor.value === sspId. Set loadingDashboardSuggestionStateFor before starting the Promise.allSettled requests, clear it in finally only if it still matches that SSP, and keep setting loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor.value = sspId after both requests settle so the deliberate partial-success behavior remains unchanged. Do not change the matched-state rules, control-id casing behavior, or the two independent Promise.allSettled request semantics. Add/update an IndexView test that mounts with dashboardSuggestionsEnabled true and config initially unfetched, resolves fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig, flushes promises, and asserts each dashboard-suggestions endpoint is called once for the SSP.

