- [medium] src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue:501 (concurrency/races): loadDashboardSuggestionState captures the SSP id at request start, but the shared useDataApi refs are still updated when that old request resolves. If the user switches SSPs while a dashboard-suggestion request for the previous SSP is in flight, the old response can overwrite pendingDashboardSuggestions/dashboardSuggestionControlResults after the new SSP has loaded; if it resolves last, the drawer can permanently show suggestions/results from the wrong SSP and loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor is set to the stale id.
- [medium] src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue:482 (correctness vs. the actual SDK/library): The new pending-suggestions fetch relies on camelcaseStopPaths like data.proposedFilterLabelSet to preserve arbitrary label keys, but camelcase-keys stopPaths are exact paths over the original object shape. For the DataResponse array returned by /dashboard-suggestions, the nested label map path is under data.<index>.proposed_filter_label_set, so these stop paths never match. Real responses can still camelize label keys such as _policy or service_name into policy/serviceName, causing the drawer to show internal labels and display mutated label keys even though formatVisibleLabelSet expects the raw keys.
